      "Northwest British Columbia Hydroelectric Facilities is a portfolio of run-of-river hydro assets totaling 303 MW in British Columbia. The assets generate under long-term electricity purchase agreements with BC Hydro, giving the portfolio a contracted operating model rather than merchant exposure. The platform is asset-heavy and geographically concentrated in British Columbia, where it forms part of the province’s privately held renewable generation base. Public announcements show that an Axium-Manulife consortium first acquired a 35% interest from AltaGas in 2018 and later agreed to acquire an additional 55% interest the same year. As a result, the consortium holds 90% of the portfolio while AltaGas retained a 10% interest, although the split between Axium-managed funds and Manulife was not publicly disclosed.",
